    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds like a pretty straightforward win, but was it really just about the laws changing? i feel like there's a lot of debate about whether all those protests actually achieved their goals or if they just shifted the problem elsewhere. what do historians say about how effective those tactics actually were in the long run?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
